- Root-cause component (service): carts
- Failure reason: high CPU/resource exhaustion due to a traffic/workload spike (manifesting as high CPU, memory, socket usage and increased latencies).
- Time of first fault evidence: ~2024-01-18T20:53:00Z (workload/latency anomalies), with continued/severe resource breaches around 2024-01-18T21:11–21:13Z.
- Supporting evidence: multiple carts KPI series (cpu, mem, socket, latency-50/90, workload) exceeded global P95 during the incident window; front-end/orders/user log.row_count spikes at ~20:53:00Z indicate an upstream traffic surge; no error logs were present, pointing to resource saturation rather than application errors.

Suggested immediate actions:
1) Scale or throttle carts (add instances or CPU) to relieve resource bottleneck.
